    <body>
    <p>The WebHelp Responsive output supports dark mode, enhancing readability and reducing eye
      strain in low-light environments.</p>
      <p><?oxy_comment_start author="Radu Pisoi" timestamp="20250710T120336+0000" comment="Not all themes support dark themes, so this parameter might be activated only for themes that has this support.

So, I this we should move last note before this sentence."?>You can enable this feature by
      setting the <ph conkeyref="reusables-webhelp-output-parameters/ph_webhelp_enable_dark_mode"/>
      parameter. Once enabled, a "Switch theme" button will appear in the header, offering three
      theme options:<?oxy_comment_end?><dl id="dl_ajk_bbp_xfc">
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Auto</dt>
          <dd>Adapts to the theme set in the browser's settings.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Light</dt>
          <dd><?oxy_comment_start author="Radu Pisoi" timestamp="20250710T132730+0000" comment="A strong word. Maybe select, switch."?>Forces<?oxy_comment_end?>
            the light mode in the interface.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt>Dark</dt>
          <dd>Forces the dark mode in the interface.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
    <p><?oxy_comment_start author="Radu Pisoi" timestamp="20250710T133142+0000" comment="If Light or Oxygen themes are not fit with your theme, you can create your own theme that support dark mode. You have two options: create a template starting from an existing one or create a template from scratch."?>You
      can enable dark mode <xref
        href="webhelp-enabling-dark-mode.dita#webhelp-enabling-dark-mode/section_snm_ckr_rfc">in a
        publishing template based on an existing template</xref> or <xref
        href="webhelp-enabling-dark-mode.dita#webhelp-enabling-dark-mode/section_wrm_4jr_rfc">in a
        publishing template created from scratch</xref>.<?oxy_comment_end?></p>
    <note id="note_eh4_l2v_lfc" type="note">Both the <b>Light</b> and <b>Oxygen</b> templates
      support light and dark modes.</note>
  </body>
